<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Profile of Ms. Patience Buhikire</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">5th Floor, Uganda Business Facilitation Centre,<br>Plot 1 Baskerville Avenue, Kololo,<br>P. O. Box 6848, Kampala.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ms. Patience Buhikire is the Acting Commissioner Legal Services.<br>She has previously served in an acting capacity whenever substantive Commissioners were away on official duty or leave, ensuring stability and seamless operations. In her new role, she will oversee the Bureau’s legal and board affairs, guaranteeing continuity, regulatory compliance, effective governance support, and the provision of sound legal guidance in the execution of URSB’s mandate.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">An Advocate of the High Court of Uganda with fourteen (14) years of experience, Ms. Buhikire is also a Commissioner for Oaths and Notary Public. She substantively serves as Assistant Commissioner Legal Services at URSB and previously headed the Legal and Advisory Services Department. She is a member of the Uganda Law Society, East African Law Society, and the Institute of Corporate Governance of Uganda.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Among her notable achievements is championing the establishment of the URSB Legal Department/Chambers, now a fully functional in-house law firm managing advisory and litigation matters. Over the past six years, she has supervised more than 90 civil cases, with 35 concluded in favour of the Bureau, saving an estimated UGX 2.5 billion in costs and damages.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">She has supported over 25 legal reforms, led the development of the annual URSB Case Digest launched in June 2025, and spearheaded the acquisition of a digital Case Management System to enhance efficiency, transparency, and supervisory oversight.</p>
		</div>

				
							<button type="button" class="pum-close popmake-close" aria-label="Close">
			x			</button>
		
	</div>

</div>
<div 
